SIMPLE: scandalously
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scandalously
<hw>Scan"dal*ous*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a manner
to give offense; shamefully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His discourse at table was <qex>scandalously</qex> unbecoming the
dignity of his station.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With a disposition to impute immorality or
wrong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shun their fault, who, <qex>scandalously</qex> nice,⟦br⟧
Will needs mistake an author into vice.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scandalousness</ent>⟦br⟧
